HEADWORD: Puppetry
<hw>Pup"pet*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Action or
appearance resembling that of a puppet, or puppet show; hence, mere form
or show; affectation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Puppetry</qex> of the English laws of divorce.</q>
<rj><qau>Chambers.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

